$ Excel function: countif

{ Count specific values

  The following example uses the → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions[sub] `testData` to fill a few values (`foo`, `bar` and `baz`) into the cells in column 1 (rows 3 through 8).

  It then uses `=countif(…)` to count the occurences of `foo`, `bar` and `baz` in the test data.

  gh|about-Excel|/functions/countif/count-specific-values.bas||

 `foo` occurs three times, `bar` once and `baz` twice:
  gh|about-Excel|/functions/countif/img/count-specific-values.png||

}
{ Count occurences of a value

 `countif` can be used to count how many times a given value appears in a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range[range].
  -
  Thus, it allows to check which value are unique within a certain range.

  In the following example, the result of `countif` shows how many times the value left of the `countif` is found in `A1:A6`.

  gh|about-Excel|/functions/countif/count-occurences.bas||

  gh|about-Excel|/functions/countif/img/count-occurences.png||

}
sa:

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/formulas/array/countifs[`countifs`] as an array formula.

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/functions[Excel functions]
